Thandokuhle Msane, 6, tragically drowned on Wednesday afternoon, 13 January, while swimming with a group of his friends in the Mnamfu river lagoon in Hibberdene. Despite the no swimming in beaches regulations,Thandokuhle and his group of friends ventured into the water. Port Shepstone Search and Rescue, K9 SAR and Medevac were called to the scene by the community. It is alleged that the boys were seen swimming in the lagoon from about two that afternoon. “It was not long thereafter that Msane got into trouble and disappeared under the water, the group of friends had immediately contacted the community, who called the police,” said police on the scene. W/O Romel Da Rose and K9 Bear made their way into the water and Bear gave an positive indication as to where the body of the young boy was. Officers then searched the area and a few minutes after the indication by Bear, the body was recovered. Thandokuhle’s body had to be carried out to the roadway across dense bush area, over a railway line and was handed over to the Hibberdene SAPS. An investigation is underway.